{"id":"mai-5rzd","kind":"decision","title":"mai pr design — lessons from git-appraise","body":"## Key lessons from git-appraise (Google)\n\n### What they got right\n1. **reviewRef + targetRef** — PR is just two branch refs. `reviewRef` = source branch, `targetRef` = where it merges. Simple, no platform coupling.\n2. **Submitted = is-ancestor check** — `repo.IsAncestor(commit, targetRef)`. No status flag to track — merge detection is a git query. Can't get out of sync.\n3. **Notes on the FIRST commit** — review request annotates the first revision. All comments for that review hang off the same commit. Clean lookup.\n4. **cat_sort_uniq merge** — same as maitake. JSON lines, append-only, deterministic merge.\n5. **Comment threading via parent/original** — `parent` = reply, `original` = edit. Exactly what we already have.\n6. **Resolved = aggregate of thread** — walks comment tree, conjunction of resolved states. Not a single flag.\n7. **Alias for rebased commits** — when review branch rebases, store the new HEAD as `alias`. Old commit still anchors the notes.\n8. **Separate refs per concern** — reviews in one ref, comments in another, CI in another. We use one ref but multiple kinds — similar separation.\n\n### What we do differently (better for our use case)\n1. **Everything in one ref** — git-appraise uses 4+ refs (reviews, discuss, ci, analyses). We use `refs/notes/maitake` for everything. Simpler push/pull, one merge.\n2. **Notes on arbitrary objects, not just commits** — git-appraise ties reviews to commits. We can attach notes to any git object, or create our own targets.\n3. **Event-sourced state** — git-appraise folds requests by timestamp (last request wins). We fold ALL fields via events. More flexible.\n4. **CRDT merge** — git-appraise has no concurrent edit story. We have YDoc.\n5. **Kind system** — git-appraise is review-only. We have tickets, docs, decisions, warnings, reviews — same substrate.\n\n### Design decisions for mai pr\n- PR is `kind: pr` with edges to source and target branches\n- `reviewRef` = current branch (auto-detected from HEAD)\n- `targetRef` = specified with `--into` (default: main)\n- Submitted detection: `git merge-base --is-ancestor` on every `mai pr ls`\n- Comments anchor to commits via Location.Commit (already have this)\n- Accept/reject = comment with resolved=true/false\n- `mai pr submit` = merge + close (or just detect merge and auto-close)","timestamp":"2026-03-29T12:19:51Z","branch":"main"}
